Class FitnessFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • FitnessFunction
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DeAlgorithm, GeneticAlgorithm, PsoAlgorithm, RandomizationAlgorithm

    public class FitnessFunction
extends java.lang.Object
    From Nature Inspired Algorithms predefined Ackley's Function coded. FitnessFunction class contains fitness function whose value will be optimized with optimization algorithms, functionality of this class involves calculating the fitness value of a chromosome and returning it.

    Since:
    07-02-2018

      • fitnessFunction

        public double fitnessFunction(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> x)
        This method takes takes an arraylist of chromosome as input and evaluates the fitness value and returns it back with rounded off value.
        Parameters:
        x - This is arraylist of chromosomes containing double values of chromosome/particle.
        Returns:
        double This is the returned fitness value rounded off to desired accuracy.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - when invoked by null ArrayList Object.
        Since:
        1.0
